Signed-off-by: CHEN, CHUN <jim60105@gmail.com>
Commented on #77 Add explanation for CUDA library dependency resolution

That's correct. If we install the necessary CUDA packages system-wide, it will require at least 800MB more of disk space. A full installation of CUDA will use over 8GB. This is the torch 2.3.1 pip package currently used by whisperX. https://pypi.org/project/torch/2.3.1/#torch-2.3.1-cp311-cp311-manylinux1_x86_64.whl METADATA Metadata-Version: 2.1 Name: torch (55 more lines were trimmed) Be aware of its dependencies, which already included the required CUDA packages. Not every version of PyTorch release has these dependencies, and I often have to check this when containerizing ML projects. I'm not entirely sure if this is suitable for the documentation, as it doesn't relate much to the project usage. I think it's a slimming technique!
